definition.value: A phenylalanine derivative that is phenylalanine in which the amino group is substituted by a [(E)-{[(Z)-2-amino-1,2-dicyanoethenyl]imino}methyl]amino group. It is a chemical intermediate for nucleotide synthesis.
An aminoimidazole that is 1H-imidazole substituted by 1-carboxy-2-phenylethyl, cyano(imino)methyl, and amino groups at positions 1, 4 and 5, respectively. It is a chemical intermediate.
A 2-oxo monocarboxylic acid anion that is the conjugate base of 2-oxooctanoic acid, obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group; major species at pH 7.3.
A class of glucoglycerolipids that consists of any 1,2-diacyl-sn-glycerol having an alpha-D-glucosyl residue attached at position 3.
